Last words from Charu: attn on marginalized groups such as men and boys, identity is not an either or in terms of attention to a cause. This is a human rights issue that affects all human beings. #ViolenceAgainstMen #OGRWebTalks

Charu: "Any response has to be survivor-centered and carried out in a survivor participatory manner (…) it is not for us to decide, it is for survivors to decide. It is a privilege for us to work with them" http://bit.ly/2Z9wavM #OGRWebTalks #violenceagainstmen
When asked for an example of something that shows what can be done, @SophieSutrich: There are some examples, but still a lot of work that needs to be done. #ViolenceAgainstMen #OGRWebTalks

Charu Lata Hogg @AllSurvivorsPro "We do not advocate for a one-size-fits-all approach" as nuance is important to understand specificities and differences between survivors. LIVE on Facebook : http://bit.ly/2Z9wavM #OGRWebTalks #violenceagainstmen @OGR_EN

Both @SophieSutrich and Charu agree over the last few years there has been a flurry of activity in the context of sexual violence in conflict. However, there is still a gap between commitment at a high level and implementation on the ground #violenceagainstmen #OGRWebTalks

In @AllSurvivorsPro's research, we have found that by using words such as humiliation and torture, men disguise the sexual nature of the violence perpetrated against them. LIVE on Facebook : http://bit.ly/2Z9wavM #OGRWebTalks #violenceagainstmen @OGR_EN

In response to which factors are most important to ending violence, @SophieSutrich says we need to adapt state laws to international standards, training armed/police forces, and make political and social commitment to the subject. #ViolenceAgainstMen #OGRWebTalks

Because women already experience gender inequality, interventions can be easier to understand than for #violenceagainstmen. There is no one size fits all approach. Treating all assault the same may not be effective for men and may erode the safe space for women. #OGRWebTalks

Charu Lata Hogg @AllSurvivorsPro underlines that the marginalisation of men & boys in humanitarian responses to #sexualviolence is linked to both prevailing gender norms and limited resources. LIVE on Facebook : http://bit.ly/2Z9wavM #OGRWebTalks #violenceagainstmen @OGR_EN

Charu: Lessons to be learned from the decades of advocacy and research that has gone into sexual violence against women and girls. However, we must understand that the motivations are different. #ViolenceAgainstMen #OGRWebTalks
. @SophieSutrich: When we train our people on sexual violence, it doesn't cost us anything to include all the different people violence is acted on. #ViolenceAgainstMen #OGRWebTalks

Charu from @AllSurvivorsPro: It's not only military conflict zones. When boys are in situations such as a refugee camp or other vulnerable situations leaves them particularly at risk. Other factors like disability, age, sex orientation add risk. #ViolenceAgainstMen #OGRWebTalks

. @SophieSutrich: Sexual violence in conflict is something that is done purposefully to gain a military advantage. This can be done against men, women, boys, and girls. Utilizing assumptions about gender roles to cause more harm is common. #ViolenceAgainstMen #OGRWebTalks
